{
  "texts": [
    "For out-of-distribution (OOD) robustness of GR models, Liu et al. [176] investigate three aspects: query variations, new query types, and new tasks.",
    "Their study showed that all types of retrieval models suffer from performance drops with query variations, indicating sensitivity to query quality and structure.",
    "However, when dealing with new query types and tasks, GR models showed different levels of adaptability, with pre-training enhancing their flexibility.",
    "The research highlights the critical need for OOD robustness in GR models for dealing with ever-changing real-world information sources.",
    "Experiments.Analyzing experimental results is essential for understanding the performance of different GR models."
  ]
}